div.p:
My Dear Mr. Secretary: I have the honor to
                            acknowledge receipt of your letter of August 27, 1921, with its
                            enclosure from the Nicaraguan Minister regarding the purchase of— 

5,000 rifles;

3,000,000 cartridges for same;

25 machine guns;

250,000 rounds of ammunition for machine guns

2 military aeroplanes, with their regulation supply of
                                    ammunition and indispensable spare parts.
